'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/daveklein/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, 'body': "### Description 
This recipe takes the output from an existing ML pipeline that has stored its results in MongoDB Atlas.  We then join two streams of that source data, perform an aggregation on the joined data, and send the results to an HTTP endpoint to trigger model retraining.  We also sink the unaggregated joined data to MongoDB Atlas to be used by the retraining process downstream (and off-camera, so to speak). 

### Github Issue
https://github.com/confluentinc/ksqldb-recipes/issues/107

### New recipe checklist

- [X] Full code validated in Confluent Cloud
- [X] SQL style/syntax consistent to existing recipes
- [X] Validate presentation with `python3 -m mkdocs serve`
- [X] File structure and content follow [template](https://github.com/confluentinc/ksqldb-recipes/tree/main/template)
- [X] Recipe added to [navigation](https://github.com/confluentinc/ksqldb-recipes/blob/main/mkdocs.yml): comment out until phase release
- [X] Spell check, e.g. using `aspell`
- [X] Source connector's auto topic naming convention works with the ksqlDB app values for `KAFKA_TOPIC`
